                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Four Power Pact/103c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="42" xml:id="d307fn42">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, June 9, to the Ambassadors in France, Great Britain, and
                        Germany and to the American delegate to the Disarmament Conference.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-09T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 9, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. The President gave out the following statement this morning: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The initialing at Rome of the Four Power Pact between France, Germany,
                            Great Britain and Italy is a good augury. The United States welcomes
                            every effort toward replacing conflicting national aims by international
                            cooperation for the greater advantage of all. This agreement of the
                            principal European Powers to work closely together for the preservation
                            of peace should give renewed courage to all who are striving for the
                            success of the Geneva and London Conferences.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please inform the Italian Government of the text of this statement, making clear
                    that you are acting under instructions from your Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
